org.jscripter.emu.java.io
Interface Serializable

All Known Implementing Classes:
Boolean, Byte, Character, Double, Enum, Float, Integer, Long, Number, Short, String, StringBuffer, StringBuilder
public interface Serializable

An internal interface that enables serializability of the class implementing, emulating java.io.Serializable.

In Java, Classes that do not implement this interface will not have any of their state serialized or deserialized. All subtypes of a serializable class are themselves serializable. The serialization interface has no methods or fields and serves only to identify the semantics of being serializable.

This interface is only used internally by JS re-compiler implementations.

Please refer to the Java API Standards for detail description of the original class or interface.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must redirect the resolution of the emulated original Java class or interface to this one.
